commit.message:
Merge pull request #3 from Livefyre/enum_string_values_from_dict

Support enum values by name.

Merge pull request #2 from Livefyre/tags_storage

Add support for extensions.
Add an option to ignore extra fields when converting dicts to PB.

Fixing issue #3 (thanks, @chicagoben)

Sub-messages would cause a TypeError to be thrown
Recursive encoding of messages no longer mutates the TYPE_CALLABLE_MAP global

Merge pull request #2 from CanalTP/master

Using enum labels wasn't recursive
README.md's code blocks are now annotated
enum_as_labels is now use_enum_labels, and defaults to False

Merge pull request #1 from CanalTP/master

Allow enum values to be written out using their label names

Support Enums as labels not ints

You need to pass enum_as_labels = True in ordre to do so
Added README.md; fixed cyclic reference to protobuf_to_dict; bumped to 0.0.2.
Fixed type map so that the various fixed types are now mapped to the appropriate Python integer type
